OL,6,FThe covers represented the whole
OL,7,Frange of BBC output ` one week it
OL,8,Fmight be a celebrity or returning
OL,9,Ffavourite, the next a children's
OL,10,Fprogramme or Radio 3 play.
OL,12,FAs late as 1988, children's
OL,13,Fprogrammes made the cover three times
OL,14,F` Going Live!, Blue Peter and The
OL,15,FChronicles of Narnia all featured.
OL,17,FIts character in the 70s and 80s
OL,18,Fstood in stark contrast to that of TV
OL,19,FTimes ` always more of a woman's
OL,20,Fmagazine than a TV guide and, in the
OL,21,Flate-80s, notably vulgar and badly
OL,22,Fdesigned too.
